To effectively monitor, control, and manage the virtual machines making up your <%= vars.app_runtime_full %> (<%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>) deployment, you may need to identify which VM corresponds to a particular job in <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>. You can find the CID of a particular VM from <%= vars.ops_manager %> by navigating to the **Status** tab in the <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> tile.

If you have deployed <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> to VMware vSphere, you can also identify which <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> job corresponds to which VM using the vCenter vSphere client.

<p class="note"><strong>Note:</strong> The CID shown in <%= vars.ops_manager %> is the name of the machine in vCenter.</p>


## <a id='id-jobs'></a> Identifying <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> Jobs Using vCenter

To identify <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> jobs using vCenter:

1. Launch the vSphere client and log in to the vCenter Server system.

1. Select the **Inventory > Hosts and Clusters** view.

    <%= image_tag("images/id/host-cluster.jpg") %>

1. Select the Resource Pool containing your <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> deployment.

    <%= image_tag("images/id/deployment.jpg") %>

1. Select the **Virtual Machines** tab.

    <%= image_tag("images/id/vm-tab.jpg") %>

1. Right-click the column label heading and check **job**.

    <%= image_tag("images/id/job.jpg") %>

1. The job column displays the <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> job associated with each virtual machine.

    <%= image_tag("images/id/jobs.jpg") %>
